{"id": "s002", "kodava": "avala noatiyand ikkathe!", "devanagari": "अवल नोअतियंड इक्कथे!", "english": "Don't keep staring at her!", "tense": "imperative_negative", "person": "nii", "confidence": "native_speaker_verified", "source": "corrections_section_b", "grammar_notes": ["avala = accusative of ava (her, direct object)", "noatiyand = progressive of noatuw'k (to look/stare)", "ikkathe = negative imperative (don't keep doing)", "WRONG: ava'k noatiyand (dative used instead of accusative)"]}
{"id": "s003", "kodava": "Naa Kodagu'nja bandhiye. Bengaluru'l ullo.", "devanagari": "ना कोदगुन्ज बंदिये. बेंगलुरुल उल्लो.", "english": "I came from Kodagu. I am in Bengaluru.", "tense": "past + present", "person": "naa", "confidence": "native_speaker_verified", "source": "corrections_grammar", "grammar_notes": ["Origin + current residence = two separate sentences", "Kodagu'nja = ablative (from Kodagu)", "bandhiye = naa past of bapp'k", "Bengaluru'l = locative (in Bengaluru)", "WRONG: Naa Kodagu'nja bandhand Bengaluru'k poayith (bad combination)"]}
